      "side": 1,
      "message": "Good news: hinting does seem to help (guess the extra logic changed the prediction weight for the existing branch?).  Doesn\u0027t completely wipe out the delta, but brings it down to ~1.5%.  Numbers for a random Lottie file on my machine:\n\nmaster (no  hints): 1178 us\nmaster (yes hints): 1170 us\nCL     (no  hints): 1209 us\nCL     (yes hints): 1187 us\n\nMike, time to bring SK_LIKELY out?  I bet we can shave a couple more % if we sprinkle magic LIKELY dust all over SkJSON :)\n\nThis is what I tried:\n\n--- a/modules/skjson/src/SkJSON.cpp\n+++ b/modules/skjson/src/SkJSON.cpp\n@@ -552,7 +552,7 @@ private:\n     consume_string:\n         while (!is_eostring(*p)) ++p;\n \n-        if (*p \u003d\u003d \u0027\"\u0027) {\n+        if (__builtin_expect(*p \u003d\u003d \u0027\"\u0027, 1)) {\n             // Valid string found.\n             func(s_begin, p - s_begin);\n             return p + 1;\n\nI think we can land this as-is and then circle back to squeeze more perf with hinting.",
